entries.headline: Phase 1: Unchecked Infestation
entries.content:
Without any true natural predators, these insects are beginning to spread rapidly throughout this region, and their massive hives serve as a magnificent example of their industriousness and social coordination.

Their queens are equally impressive. I have witnessed more than one creature fall victim to their venomous sting.

entries.headline: Phase 1: Insect Aggression
entries.content:
I have observed these flying insects for quite some time, and I have been very impressed with their intelligence and advanced communal behaviors.

They are also unbelievably aggressive, and none more than their formidable queen. I have seen more than one unsuspecting predator fall prey to her deadly sting. So exhilarating!
